dataIdInfo.idAbs: Location of boundary fences that are publicly managed by the ACT Government. Attributes include: boundary fence ID, IAMS ID (BND), division name, boundary type (eg agricultural, bollard, pipe etc), purpose (eg boundary, internal, vehicle etc), construction wire (eg net, pailing, pfp etc), construction post (eg concrete, hardwood, steel etc), construction end (eg hardwood, steel, treated pine etc), owner, terrain (eg flat, steep, undulating etc), vegetation type (eg heavy forest, improved pasture or native grassland etc), condition (eg fair, good, very poor etc), length and dataset entry creation date. These assets are managed by Parks and Territory Services (PATS), within TAMS. The PATS branch is therefore the source of asset data. The data is then managed in the Integrated Asset Management System (IAMS) on behalf of PATS by the Asset Information and Management Services Branch.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Locations of boundary fences across the Australian Capital Territory
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Territory and Municipal Services, Parks and Territory Services

Consts.useLimit: Direct access to data within the ACT Integrated Asset Management System (IAMS) is limited to internal users. The custodian is responsible for the maintenance and distribution of the data. The distribution of data to external users can usually be done in any format compatible with Oracle OSD software or capable of being converted using FME software, subject to custodian approval.

ConResult.conExpl: Although this dataset is updated on a regular basis it will always have a backlog of entries hence it is not a true reflection of the all the government owned assets depicted in this dataset. Similar assets within the Australian Capital Territory that are owned and/or managed privately or by other agencies or state government are also excluded. Some locations are indicative depending on the underlying systems that they are managed by or how the data was captured. Data may also be omitted from the dataset if it refers to an asset that is not currently operational.

dataLineage.statement:
The dataset titled CGDMGA.BOUNDARY_FENCE is maintained in the Integrated Asset Management System (IAMS) by the Asset Information and Management Services Branch within Territory and Municipal Services (TAMS) on behalf of Parks and Territory Services (PATS). The information is sourced from audits undertaken by asset maintenance staff within PATS and from Works As Executed drawings provided by contractors. The raw data is then processed by officers within Asset Information and Management Services to conform to the IAMS Oracle database (Oracle SDO version 11.2) used for the ACT Government Integrated Asset Management System (IAMS). The IAMS stores data in the ACT Stromlo Projection. Spatial layers within the IAMS are created from Oracle views, effectively joining the spatial table to an Asset Inventory table using system generated unique identifiers. Spatial layers are points, lines or polygons, tested for valid or invalid geometries in ESRI ArcGIS software (version 10.3.1).
Since 1995, fence data was collected by staff, students and others uisng GPS "Garmin GPS II Plus" to collect points along fence, mainly strainers and gates. Downloaded in PCX5 and converted to Arcview with GarmapXL. Points converted into lines by heads up digitising on the screen at about 1 to 4,000 metre scale. Attributes added in Arcview and Excel. Process completed by G. Hirth.
